/*
 * $Id: ChangeLog,v 1.4833 2006/02/22 04:10:30 ronpinkas Exp $
 */

/* Use this format for the entry headers:
   YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM UTC[-|+]hhmm Your Full Name <your_email@address>
   For example:
   2002-12-01 23:12 UTC+0100 Foo Bar <foo.bar@foobar.org>
*/

2006-02-22 17:50 UTC+0300 Phil Krylov <phil a t newstar.rinet.ru>
  * source/debug/debugger.prg
    ! Try harder to deremine valid stop lines.

2006-02-21 20:08 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <Ron in xHarbour.com>
  * makefile.vc
    + Added hbdead.c and hbstripl.c to harbour.exe generation.

2006-02-21 19:29 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <Ron in xHarbour.com>
  * include/simplex.c
    * Removed support for MAX_STREAM in favor of new STREAM_SIZE_ALLOC
    * Improved sPair to use malloc()/realloc() instead of fixed size stack memory

  * source/compiler/hbslex.c
  * source/macro/macroslx.c
    - Removed no longer supported MAX_STREAM

  * source/compiler/harbour.slx
  * source/macro/macro.slx
    * Fixed GPF trap in STREAM_APPEND()

2006-02-21 17:33 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <Ron in xHarbour.com>
  * include/hbvm.h
  * source/vm/hvm.c
    + added hb_vmRequest( USHORT uiRequest )
  * source/vm/estack.c
    + Added Save/Reset/Restore of HVM's s_uiActionRequest
      so that Desructors are never interrupted from being executed.
  * source/rtl/errorsys.prg
    + Added reset of DispBegin()s (thnx to Leo Letendre)

2006-02-21 23:05 UTC+0100 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * xharbour/source/compiler/hbfix.c
    ! fixed stupid typo in copy and past which broke conditional jump
      reduction

2006-02-21 20:20 UTC+0100 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * xharbour/make_tgz.sh
  * xharbour/xharbour.spec
    * removed not longer used HB_FM_STATISTICS_OFF macro

  * xharbour/bin/hb-func.sh
    * added support for -L<librarypath> in xhbmk

  * xharbour/contrib/mysql/mysql.c
    * minor modification to eliminate accessing uninitialized variable

  * xharbour/contrib/rdd_ads/Makefile
    * removed not longer necessary MT version of ADS RDD
      Please make the same in non GNU Makefiles. As I can see many of
      libraries are build in two version when in fact they not have MT
      dependent code.

  * xharbour/contrib/rdd_ads/ads1.c
  * xharbour/contrib/rdd_ads/adsfunc.c
    * removed some unnecessary #include ...

  * xharbour/include/gtinfo.h
    - removed not longer used GTI_XCURSOR*
    + added GTI_CURSORBLINKRATE to control cursor blinking frequency in milliseconds

  * xharbour/include/hbapicdp.h
  * xharbour/source/rtl/cdpapi.c
    * added UTF8 related functions: hb_cdpUTF8StringLength(),
      hb_cdpStringInUTF8Length(), hb_cdpUTF8ToStrn().
    * Changed name of hb_cdpStrnToUTF() function to hb_cdpStrnToUTF8()
      to avoid confusions with UTF16

  * xharbour/include/hberrors.h
  * xharbour/source/compiler/hbgenerr.c
    + added to new errors (memory corruption and memory overflow) for
      compiler level FM statistic.

  * xharbour/source/common/hbver.c
    * reenabled memory statistic information in compiler build info.

  * xharbour/source/compiler/harbour.c
    + added FM statistic module -  when harbour.c is compiled with
      HB_FM_STATISTICS macro then it uses memory statistics like the
      one used by HVM. There is many of memory leaks in xHarbour
      compiler which have to be fixed. Recently Ryszard cleared all
      memory leeks in Harbour so it will be good to borrow this
      modifications.
    ! fixed hb_conOutErr() to properly display data when given size is 0

  * xharbour/source/ct/Makefile
    * Removed unnecessary MT version of CT library - it also does not have
      any MT code.

  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtxwc/gtxwc.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtxwc/gtxwc.h
    * added support for clipboard
    * added support for cursor shape - like in DOS/VGA

2006-02-21 17:50 UTC+0300 Phil Krylov <phil a t newstar.rinet.ru>
  * source/compiler/harbour.sly
    ! Don't suppress line number generation after RETURN statements.
      This fixes code like:
          CASE <expr>
            RETURN
          CASE 1 == NIL /* wrong lineno in error msg */

2006-02-17 16:45 UTC-0300 Eduardo Fernandes <modalsist@yahoo.com.br>
  * make_pc.bat
    ! minor fix in the clean session.

2006-02-16 20:53 UTC-0500 Gerald Drouillard <Gerald@drouillard.ca>
  * xharbour/source/tip/ftpcln.prg
    ! fix :mget().  It now uses :downloadfile() instead of :retr()

2006-02-16 18:30 UTC+0100 Mauricio Abre <mgabre@gmail.com>
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtalleg/ssf.h
    * Added set_clip_rect #define for allegro 4.2

2006-02-15 22:30 UTC+0100 Mauricio Abre <mgabre@gmail.com>
  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtalleg/gtalleg.c
    * Fixed broken compilation

2006-02-15 20:30 UTC+0100 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * xharbour/xharbour.spec
  * xharbour/bin/hb-func.sh
    * some modification in xhb* scripts building - adding passing
      predefined compiler and linker switches, higher priority
      to user libraries specified by -l<libname> linker option
      given

  * xharbour/include/hbcomp.h
  * xharbour/include/hbpp.h
  * xharbour/source/compiler/cmdcheck.c
  * xharbour/source/compiler/genc.c
  * xharbour/source/compiler/harbour.slx
  * xharbour/source/compiler/harbour.sly
  * xharbour/source/compiler/hbpcode.c
  * xharbour/source/macro/macro.y
  * xharbour/source/pp/ppcomp.c
  * xharbour/source/pp/ppcore.c
  * xharbour/source/pp/pragma.c
  * xharbour/source/rdd/workarea.c
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbffpt/dbffpt1.c
    * moved most of extern declaration to header files

  * xharbour/source/compiler/harbour.c
    * disable line striping optimization when -l compiler switch
      (suppress line number information) is set - in such case
      it's only waste of time

  * xharbour/samples/sitesvr/sitesvr.prg
    * formatting

  * xharbour/source/rtl/regex.c
    ! fixed size of given string setting

  * xharbour/source/rtl/gtalleg/gtalleg.c
    * check if allegro initialization success at startup to avoid GPF
      when allegro cannot be initialized

  * xharbour/source/vm/errorapi.c
    * increased output error buffer

2006-02-15 09:35 UTC-0300 Eduardo Fernandes <modalsist@yahoo.com.br>
  * make_b32.bat
  * make_pc.bat
    + added sixcdx.lib and sixcdxmt.lib in clean entry.

