  * source/vm/dbgentry.c
    ! Fixed debugging of expressions with field references.

2006-02-14 22:50 UTC-0100 Ath <Ath1 at sourceforge.net>
  * xharbour/makefile.bc
    * Obviously I made a bad merge, sorry, fixed

2006-02-14 08:45 UTC-0300 Eduardo Fernandes <modalsist@yahoo.com.br>
  * makefile.pc
    + added hbdead.c and hbstripl.c to harbour.exe generation.

2006-02-13 22:12 UTC-0600 Vicente Guerra <vicente@guerra.com.mx>
  * ./makefile.bc
    * Added hbdead.c and hbstripl.c to harbour.exe generation.

2006-02-14 02:30 UTC+0100 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * xharbour/include/hbapi.h
    ! fixed some macros to return boolean value - on systems where
      BOOL type is not mapped to int the old versions may not work
      properly

  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbcmd.c
    * fixed GPF in DBF2TEXT when work are is not in use.

  * xharbour/source/rtl/dbdelim.prg
    * generate 2001 RT error when work are not in used before
      export file is created.

  * xharbour/source/vm/errorapi.c
    * set DOSERROR() to oError:OSCODE when RT error is generated
      It's documented Clipper behavior.

  * xharbour/source/vm/extend.c
    + added hb_extIsObject() which works like existing hb_extIsArray()

2006-02-14 01:50 UTC-0100 Ath <Ath1 at sourceforge.net>
  * xharbour/hrbdll.*
  * xharbour/makefile.*
    * add sixcdx.lib to all makefiles, generates a separate .lib file

2006-02-13 23:30 UTC+0100 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * xharbour/include/hbcomp.h
  * xharbour/source/compiler/Makefile
  * xharbour/source/compiler/cmdcheck.c
  * xharbour/source/compiler/genc.c
  * xharbour/source/compiler/harbour.c
  * xharbour/source/compiler/harbour.sly
  * xharbour/source/compiler/hbfix.c
  * xharbour/source/compiler/hbpcode.c
  * xharbour/source/compiler/hbusage.c
  + xharbour/source/compiler/hbdead.c
  + xharbour/source/compiler/hbstripl.c
    + added dead code eliminator (f.e. inside WHILE .F. / IF .F. blocks)
    + added repeated HB_P_LINE* pcodes stripping - the can appear after
      dead code elimination
    + added optimization for WHILE .T. / IF .T.
    * added -kJ switch which disable jump optimization
      (works like in Harbour)
    * restored BEGIN SEQUENCE / RECOVER / END elimination with empty
      SEQUENCE body
    * rewritten jump optimization to to support multi passes

  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbf1.c
    * enabled 'Y' (currency) field support - mapped to double

  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbcmd.c
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbsort.prg
  * xharbour/source/rdd/hbdbsort.c
    ! fixed some bugs in sort command

  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbstrux.prg
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbtotal.prg
    - removed no longer necessary using of temporary aliases

  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbffpt/dbffpt1.c
    * casting

  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbfntx/dbfntx1.c
    * disabled validation of unused index pages - Clipper left them
      dirty so xHarbour reported that index is corrupted

  * xharbour/source/vm/fm.c
    ! fixed pointer updating in memory statistic presentation on machines
      with strict alignment

  * xharbour/xharbour.spec
  * xharbour/bin/pack_bin.bat
  * xharbour/bin/pack_src.bat
    * updated version number to 0.99.61

2006-02-13 04:15 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <Ron in xHarbour.com>
  * include/hbver.h
    * Increased to 0.99.61

2006-02-11 16:10 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <Ron in xHarbour.com>
  * source/pp/pptable.c
    + Added support for TEXT INTO <LValue>
  * source/vm/hvm.c
    + Added __TEXTINTO() to siupport implementation of new TEXT INTO command
  + tests/gui_ie.prg
    + New sample of TEXT INTO command

2006-02-10 13:31 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <Ron in xHarbour.com>
  * source/rtl/win32ole.prg
    * Enhanced support of BYREF arguments

  * source/vm/errorapi.c
    ! Fixed internal error when C code calls the error system after a pending request from prior error.

2006-02-09 09:13 UTC-0500 Gerald Drouillard <gerald@drouillard.ca>
  * source/rtl/tbrowse.prg
    ! Fix for :setcolpos() changed line:
         if ! ::stable .AND. nColPos >= 1 .AND. nColPos <= ::nColumns
      to
         if ::lNeverDisplayed .OR. (! ::stable .AND. nColPos <= ::rightVisible .AND. nColPos >= ::leftVisible)
      as this shortcut would mess up the tbrowse if the colpos was set outside left and right visible columns.

